        {
          "id": "ba854d9afaf6_3",
          "href": null,
          "name": "8e31",
          "text": "“Being on the path of a pilgrimage, dreams which have been dormant for a long time come alive again helped along by the steady rhythm of walking, the sound of footsteps and the simplicity of life. It is the Earth itself which, inside of us, awakens an age old dream to new life. I often have vivid dreams of a large peace movement. The walking itself and the connection to the fellow pilgrim open up a special quality in communication. One experiences a feeling of belonging to something one loves. Maybe it is only through walking that the system of the cells recalls a long forgotten past when as nomads we were connected to Mother Earth and all of Creation.”",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
