            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "ba854d9afaf6_6",
          "href": null,
          "name": "2557",
          "text": "The pilgrim walks each step in humility and gratitude for the gift of life. The pilgrim walks lightly upon the Earth. All of the world’s major religions have their own, or share, sacred sites that have been the focal point for pilgrimages for hundreds of years and often for millennia.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "ba854d9afaf6_7",
          "href": null,
          "name": "195c",
          "text": "Christians, Jews and Muslims all share common pilgrimage routs to the holy land. There are many traditional pilgrimage destinations in Buddhism, among them Lumbini as the birthplace of the Buddha and Bodhgaya as the place of Buddha’s enlightenment. Famous Christian pilgrimages are the road to Santiago de Campostela and the holy springs at Lourdes.",
          "metadata": null,
