        {
          "id": "ba854d9afaf6_10",
          "href": null,
          "name": "ed12",
          "text": "This is precisely where one of the transformative powers of engaging in pilgrimage lies: respect. Being a pilgrim is to walk in the full awareness that every step we take, wherever we place our foot on planet Earth, we are stepping on sacred ground and we should do so in gratitude and humility.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "ba854d9afaf6_11",
          "href": null,
          "name": "aca9",
          "text": "In his book Earth Pilgrim, Satish Kumar explores the inner and outer aspects of pilgrimage. He believes that: “To be a pilgrim is to be on a path of adventure, to move out of our comfort zones, to let go of our prejudices and preconditioning, to make strides towards the unknown.” In taking on a pilgrims attitude its is important to go beyond ideas of good and evil, and to be dedicated to our natural calling.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
